Method Detail

callsTo

public <T> T callsTo(Class<T> clazz)
Generates a proxy object for use with other Funcito function-object generating static calls. This proxy should not be used for any other purposes. An example of proper usage (using Google Guava) is as follows:

MyClass callsTo = callsTo(MyClass.class);
Function func = functionFor( callsTo.noArgMethodWithRetType() );

In the above example, the limitation is that MyClass has to be proxyable by the current Proxy provider (see Funcito.FUNCITO_PROXY_PROVIDER_PROP). Generally this means interfaces, or non-private non-static non-final classes.
